torrhoea make me think of conditions related to the hypothalamus, since both are associated with hypothalamic-pituitary axis disorders.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051581,0.08865,0.096884,0.1105,0.10058,0.096295,0.098587,0.08612,0.078412,0.077848,0.063125,0.051421],"unified_progress":[0.042165,0.075887,0.092465,0.1047,0.10277,0.10105,0.10014,0.092632,0.086409,0.083666,0.066109,0.052014]},{"section":6,"text":"Galactorrhoea is typically due to hyperprolactinemia, which is often caused by a prolactin-secreting pituitary tumor, like a prolactinoma.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032117,0.056489,0.077412,0.089716,0.10313,0.10775,0.10896,0.10679,0.10019,0.087441,0.070246,0.059761],"unified_progress":[0.034926,0.063558,0.084282,0.095052,0.1016,0.11082,0.10536,0.10108,0.094185,0.086139,0.06957,0.053426]},{"section":7,"text":"Menstrual irregularities can also be linked to hormonal imbalances, possibly from the same cause.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040217,0.059922,0.076129,0.087176,0.094267,0.098593,0.10303,0.10112,0.097743,0.095148,0.079569,0.067086],"unified_progress":[0.042335,0.066836,0.081826,0.092206,0.096812,0.10029,0.10082,0.099842,0.095025,0.089548,0.075771,0.058692]},{"section":8,"text":"The headaches could be related to increased intracranial pressure, which is sometimes seen in pituitary tumors, especially if the tumor is large enough to press on the brainstem or surrounding structures.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039301,0.055376,0.073139,0.085782,0.094989,0.1009,0.10527,0.10499,0.10079,0.094617,0.078838,0.066009],"unified_progress":[0.039666,0.063038,0.081792,0.092523,0.09834,0.10275,0.10275,0.10096,0.096957,0.089904,0.07439,0.056926]},{"section":9,"text":"Bitemporal superior quadrantopia suggests that the optic nerves are involved.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038909,0.05